    <!-- BEAUTY ENCYCLOPEDIA -->
    <div class="encyclopedia">
        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Makeup Placement Guide</h2>
            <h3>Blush Placement by Face Shape</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Round:</b> Higher on the cheekbones, angled slightly up toward the temples to lift.</li>
                <li><b>Oval:</b> Center of the cheeks, blended outward for a soft, natural flush.</li>
                <li><b>Square:</b> Focus on the apples and blend in circular motions to soften angles.</li>
                <li><b>Heart:</b> Slightly lower on the cheeks to balance a wider forehead.</li>
                <li><b>Diamond:</b> On the tops of the cheeks, blended outward to soften sharpness.</li>
                <li><b>Long:</b> More horizontal placement across the cheeks to visually shorten the face.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Highlighter Placement</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Top of cheekbones, bridge of nose (lightly), cupid’s bow, inner corners of eyes.</li>
                <li>Avoid heavy highlight on textured areas to keep skin looking smooth.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Contour Basics</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Under cheekbones, sides of nose, jawline, and temples (lightly).</li>
                <li>Cream contour = more natural; powder contour = more defined.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Eyeshadow & Eye Shape</h2>
            <h3>General Tips</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Light shades on the lid, medium in the crease, dark on the outer corner.</li>
                <li>Shimmer on the center of the lid or inner corner for brightness.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>By Eye Shape</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Hooded:</b> Blend shadow slightly above the natural crease so it shows when eyes are open.</li>
                <li><b>Almond:</b> Most looks work; emphasize outer V for depth.</li>
                <li><b>Round:</b> Focus on elongating with outer corner depth and soft wings.</li>
                <li><b>Downturned:</b> Lift outer corners with upward-blended shadow and liner.</li>
                <li><b>Monolid:</b> Gradient washes of color and shimmer across the lid look stunning.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Lip Shapes & Enhancing Tips</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Thin Lips:</b> Overline slightly with a lip liner close to your natural shade, gloss in the center.</li>
                <li><b>Full Lips:</b> Use deeper liners and matte or satin finishes for definition.</li>
                <li><b>Uneven Lips:</b> Balance by slightly overlining the thinner side.</li>
                <li><b>Downturned Corners:</b> Avoid dark shades only on the outer corners; highlight the center.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Color Theory & Undertones</h2>
            <h3>Cool Undertones</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Best in blue-based reds, pinks, plums, cool browns, silver jewelry.</li>
                <li>Eyeshadow: taupe, mauve, cool greys, soft plum.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Warm Undertones</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Best in corals, peaches, warm reds, gold jewelry.</li>
                <li>Eyeshadow: bronze, copper, warm browns, olive.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Neutral Undertones</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Can wear both cool and warm tones; neutral browns and rose shades are especially flattering.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Haircut & Styling Theory</h2>
            <h3>By Face Shape</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Round:</b> Long layers, volume at the crown, avoid heavy width at the cheeks.</li>
                <li><b>Square:</b> Soft waves, side parts, curtain bangs to soften angles.</li>
                <li><b>Heart:</b> Chin-length layers, side-swept bangs to balance forehead and chin.</li>
                <li><b>Long:</b> Layers and waves to add width, avoid too much length without shape.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>By Hair Texture</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Straight:</b> Blunt cuts, glass hair, or soft layers for movement.</li>
                <li><b>Wavy:</b> Long layers, shag cuts, and curtain bangs enhance natural texture.</li>
                <li><b>Curly/Coily:</b> Layered cuts, shape-focused cuts, and moisture-heavy routines.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Skincare Ingredient Dictionary</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Hyaluronic Acid:</b> Hydration, plumps the skin.</li>
                <li><b>Niacinamide:</b> Reduces redness, regulates oil, refines pores.</li>
                <li><b>Vitamin C:</b> Brightening, antioxidant, helps with dark spots.</li>
                <li><b>Retinol:</b> Anti-aging, texture, acne (use at night, slowly introduce).</li>
                <li><b>AHA (Glycolic/Lactic):</b> Exfoliates surface, brightens dull skin.</li>
                <li><b>BHA (Salicylic):</b> Unclogs pores, great for acne-prone skin.</li>
                <li><b>Ceramides:</b> Strengthen skin barrier, great for dryness and sensitivity.</li>
                <li><b>Centella/ Cica:</b> Soothing, calming for sensitive or irritated skin.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Nails & Aesthetic Vibes</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Clean girl:</b> Short, rounded, milky or sheer pink nails.</li>
                <li><b>Soft girl:</b> Pastel colors, tiny hearts, soft gradients.</li>
                <li><b>Coquette:</b> Bows, lace patterns, soft pinks and whites.</li>
                <li><b>Classy:</b> French tips, nudes, deep reds.</li>
                <li><b>Glam:</b> Chrome, glitter, rhinestones, long shapes.</li>
                <li><b>Y2K:</b> Bright colors, stickers, funky French tips.</li>
                <li><b>Baddie:</b> Long acrylics, sharp shapes, bold colors.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Fragrance Families & Mood</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Floral:</b> Romantic, soft, feminine (rose, jasmine, peony).</li>
                <li><b>Fresh:</b> Clean, energizing (citrus, aquatic, green notes).</li>
                <li><b>Sweet/Gourmand:</b> Cozy, playful (vanilla, caramel, tonka bean).</li>
                <li><b>Woody:</b> Grounded, sophisticated (sandalwood, cedar, vetiver).</li>
                <li><b>Spicy/Oriental:</b> Warm, sensual (amber, spices, incense).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ency-section">
            <h2>Glow-Up Routine Ideas</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Consistent skincare routine (AM + PM) for at least 4–6 weeks.</li>
                <li>Hydration: water, herbal teas, hydrating foods.</li>
                <li>Sleep: aim for 7–9 hours with a calming night routine.</li>
                <li>Movement: light exercise or stretching to boost circulation.</li>
                <li>Grooming: brows, nails, hair trims, lip care.</li>
                <li>Style: build a small capsule wardrobe that fits your aesthetic.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

